{"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContextRef\/pushThreadDefault()"},"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContextRef","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContextRef\/MainContextProtocol-Implementations"]]},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Acquires "},{"code":"context","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and sets it as the thread-default context for the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"current thread. This will cause certain asynchronous operations","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"(such as most "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"..\/gio\/index.html"},{"type":"text","text":"-based I\/O) which are"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"started in this thread to run under ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"context"},{"type":"text","text":" and deliver their"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"results to its main loop, rather than running under the global"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"default main context in the main thread. Note that calling this function","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"changes the context returned by [func","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.MainContext.get_thread_default"},{"text":"],","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"not the one returned by [func","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.MainContext.default"},{"text":"], so it does not","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"affect the context used by functions like [func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.idle_add"},{"type":"text","text":"]."}],"sections":[],"metadata":{"symbolKind":"method","title":"pushThreadDefault()","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"extendedModule":"GLib","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"pushThreadDefault","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"()","kind":"text"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Method","role":"symbol","externalID":"s:4GLib19MainContextProtocolPAAE17pushThreadDefaultyyF::SYNTHESIZED::s:4GLib14MainContextRefV"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"pushThreadDefault","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"()","kind":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Normally you would call this function shortly after creating a new","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"thread, passing it a [struct"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"] which will be run by a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[struct"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainLoop","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"] in that thread, to set a new default context for all"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"async operations in that thread. In this case you may not need to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"ever call [method","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.MainContext.pop_thread_default","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"], assuming you want","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the new [struct"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"] to be the default for the whole lifecycle"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of the thread."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you don’t have control over how the new thread was created (e.g."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"in the new thread isn’t newly created, or if the thread life"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"cycle is managed by a ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPool","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":"), it is always suggested to wrap","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the logic that needs to use the new [struct"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","isActive":true},{"text":"] inside a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.MainContext.push_thread_default"},{"text":"] \/","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.MainContext.pop_thread_default"},{"type":"text","text":"] pair, otherwise threads that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"are re-used will end up never explicitly releasing the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"[struct","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","isActive":true},{"text":"] reference they hold.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In some cases you may want to schedule a single operation in a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"non-default context, or temporarily use a non-default context in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the main thread. In that case, you can wrap the call to the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"asynchronous operation inside a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"code":"GLib.MainContext.push_thread_default","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] \/"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.MainContext.pop_thread_default"},{"type":"text","text":"] pair, but it is up to you to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"ensure that no other asynchronous operations accidentally get","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"started while the non-default context is active."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Beware that libraries that predate this function may not correctly","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"handle being used from a thread with a thread-default context. For example,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"see "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_file_supports_thread_contexts()"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/maincontextref\/pushthreaddefault()"]}],"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/ThreadPool":{"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"ThreadPool","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPool","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ThreadPool","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/threadpool","abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GThreadPool"},{"text":" struct represents a thread pool.","type":"text"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ThreadPool","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/MainContext":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"MainContext","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/maincontext","role":"symbol","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MainContext","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"GMainContext","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" struct is an opaque data","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"type representing a set of sources to be handled in a main loop."}],"title":"MainContext","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/MainContextRef":{"role":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/maincontextref","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContextRef","abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"code":"GMainContext","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" struct is an opaque data"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"type representing a set of sources to be handled in a main loop."}],"fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"MainContextRef"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MainContextRef"}],"kind":"symbol","title":"MainContextRef"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/MainLoop":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/mainloop","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"GMainLoop","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" struct is an opaque data type"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"representing the main event loop of a GLib or GTK application.","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"MainLoop","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainLoop","title":"MainLoop","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MainLoop","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","title":"GLib","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib","abstract":[]},"../gio/index.html":{"identifier":"..\/gio\/index.html","title":"Gio","url":"..\/gio\/index.html","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"Gio","type":"text"}]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/MainContextRef/pushThreadDefault()":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContextRef\/pushThreadDefault()","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Acquires "},{"code":"context","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and sets it as the thread-default context for the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"current thread. This will cause certain asynchronous operations"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(such as most "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"..\/gio\/index.html","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"-based I\/O) which are"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"started in this thread to run under "},{"code":"context","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and deliver their"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"results to its main loop, rather than running under the global"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"default main context in the main thread. Note that calling this function"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"changes the context returned by [func"},{"code":"GLib.MainContext.get_thread_default","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"],"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"not the one returned by [func"},{"code":"GLib.MainContext.default","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"], so it does not","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"affect the context used by functions like [func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.idle_add"},{"type":"text","text":"]."}],"type":"topic","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"pushThreadDefault","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"()","kind":"text"}],"title":"pushThreadDefault()","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/maincontextref\/pushthreaddefault()"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/MainContextRef/MainContextProtocol-Implementations":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/maincontextref\/maincontextprotocol-implementations","role":"collectionGroup","title":"MainContextProtocol Implementations","type":"topic","kind":"article","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContextRef\/MainContextProtocol-Implementations"}}}